item.title: Psychedelic Velveeta! 11-11-2009 Aliens live in the second hour.
item.description: Aliens live in the second hour. Aliens are: Blake - Guitar,Bass, Vocals, Spacey odds and ends. Cameron - Drums and coolness. Venue - The Nestor Tavern 11-12-2009 10pm CST PA Engineer/Promoter - Bryan Grobe Recording Engineer - Randy Shone And yes the drums did drop out in one song. That's live for ya. :o)

item.title: The Black Angels Live in Fargo, ND
item.description: Here are The Black Angels Live here in Fargo, ND at The Aquarium. If you missed this show, try and find them playing near you and if they aren't take a listen! They are GREAT in concert! Thank you again to The Black Angels for allowing us to record them and broadcast it! Thank you to The Aquarium for letting us record also!

item.title: Open Mind! - Dead Meadow Live
item.description: Thank you to Dead Meadow and the Aquarium for allowing us to come in and tape the concert. Your hospitality was and is appreciated by all of us in the audience. We had a great time! Hope to see you far out gents again someday. And yes you will hear the soundboard start to melt down towards the end of the show. It was loud! Very loud! Stay tuned Space Cadets we have permission to tape 2 more bands in the next few weeks. More details to follow.... If your band has a concert recording you would like to air it. Just let us know. We would be happy to air it over the airwaves! Cheers, The Captain!
